<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Belhaven on 03-29-2002 12:02 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">  [QUOTE]Originally posted by Phalia:
[b]So my question to you all is..Does my guild continue to respect the list, and hope that when my turn comes, I have the forces the fastest?  Or do I take my guild to SF and make them hunt wurms for a week, and possibly get branded as KS'ers?[/b][/QUOTE]

Might I suggest that those of you on your server who support a list keep sufficient force in the zone such that those who do NOT want to use the list dont stand the chance of getting the mob?  Suppose each guild supporting the list gave a group of characters (for a week, say) to the Policing of the List, and those folks were ALWAYS there and ready to kill him. (arranging folks so that you're not on 24 hours but that you always have coverage) Then when he pops they KILL him for the next cleric on the list.  Assuming they avoid a KS (and if they're READY they probably will) what can the other folks do but complain, or attempt to KS or Ninja the loot?  If they KS or Ninja the loot, then /petition and get the GMs to clean out those who offend. 

Sure, they'll occasionally get one. But if you keep at it where they can't just walk over you, you'll be happier with the epic's you've gotten and perhaps, just perhaps , they'll have joined the rotation to avoid the hassles.

(Unfortunately, a lot of these types of players see this as a competition between you and them that they *must* win...expect it to take quite a while to wear them down)

[This message has been edited by Belhaven (edited 03-29-2002).]</TEXTAREA>
